=== New RPC ===
update_deal_pricing_v1(p_deal_id uuid, p_fields jsonb)
  - SECURITY DEFINER, authenticated only
  - workspace write lock enforced via check_workspace_write_allowed_v1()
  - writes to deal_inputs only -- creates new row, does not overwrite history
  - updates deals.assumptions_snapshot_id to new row
  - updates deals.updated_at and deals.row_version
  - allowed keys: arv, ask_price, repair_estimate, mao, multiplier
  - all fields numeric -- validated safely before insert
  - omitted key = carry forward from base snapshot
  - explicit null = remove key from assumptions
  - same-value no-op = VALIDATION_ERROR
  - missing base deal_inputs row = NOT_FOUND (no auto-create)
  - uses clock_timestamp() for deterministic row ordering within transactions

=== Corrective Notes ===
Two corrective fixes applied after initial migration:
1. DROP FUNCTION added at top of migration to ensure clean replacement
   (CREATE OR REPLACE unreliable when function evolved across multiple edits)
2. clock_timestamp() used instead of now() for deal_inputs.created_at
   (now() returns transaction timestamp -- same value for all calls in same transaction,
   causing non-deterministic ORDER BY created_at DESC, id DESC in tests)
Both fixes are in forward migrations -- no retro-edits to applied migrations.

